g.text: ALE is connected to the original non-standard system ROM,
connected to a 2nd ~CE~ to disable the chip when ALE is high,
but no common devices have such a pin.
ALE should be left not-connected during normal read-only
operation with a standard part like 28C256.
The normal ~OE~ and ~CS~ signals suffice to enable
& disable the part at the right times.
